Exception Hierarchy in Java:
In the java exception class hierarchy, the class at the top is the Throwable class, which is a
direct subclass of the Object class. Throwable has two direct subclasses Exception and Error,
which has again respective sub-classes The diagram below shows the standard exception and error
classes defined in Java, organized in the Java exceptions hierarchy:

link : https://interviewnoodle.com/exception-in-java-89a0b41e0c45

Error: Error caused by the lack of system resources such as heap memory is not
available etc. Errors are non-recoverable. During the runtime of a program if
any error occurs we will not be able to handle it.

